<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7751&amp;p=79388#p79388"><![CDATA[
<div class="quotetitle">Duck_tech wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />I have exactly same problem: can't really understand UNROM schematics from wiki for example. How it is suppossed to make last bank always visible with an OR gate connected like that? Well, i don't quite understand how it is connected... <img src="http://forums.nesdev.com/images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif" alt=":D" title="Very Happy" /><br /></div><br />When accessing $8000-$BFFF, PRG A14 is low, when accessing $C000-$FFFF, it's high. If you OR A14 with the bank index, the result will always be all 1's when accessing $C000-$FFFF. That's how the last bank gets hardwired to the top half of the addressing space.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=95">tokumaru</a> — Tue Jun 07, 2011 1:46 pm</p><hr />
